body:
GitHub Pages needed lifecycle prominence, cleaner sections, and a scannable PR/issue list for direct GitHub navigation.

## Changes

### Navigation & hero
- Lifecycle page moved to first position in nav with highlight styling
- Primary CTA changed from "Meet the Agents" to "See the Lifecycle"
- Timeline nav renamed "Recent Activity"

![Navigation with lifecycle first](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/36451f57-b64b-4194-a514-9b0dc5b863fa)

### Timeline ‚Üí PR/issue list
Replaced verbose timeline with clean list combining PRs and issues:
- 20 most recent items, chronologically sorted
- Icons (üîÄ PR, üìã Issue), state indicators (‚úÖ/‚ùå/üîµ), bot badges ü§ñ
- Direct GitHub links, readable dates

![Clean PR/issue list](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/9f598ffb-ea6c-4dff-a8dd-780c15b038f6)

### Learnings & goal sections
- Learnings: removed frequency details, simplified to stats + source types
- Goal: removed progress bar, moved below learnings

## Implementation

```javascript
// script.js - New timeline loader
async function loadTimeline() {
  const [issuesData, prsData] = await Promise.all([
    fetch('data/issues.json').then(r => r.ok ? r.json() : []),
    fetch('data/pulls.json').then(r => r.ok ? r.json() : [])
  ]);

  const combined = [
    ...issuesData.map(item => ({ ...item, type: 'issue' })),
    ...prsData.map(item => ({ ...item, type: 'pr' }))
  ].sort((a, b) => new Date(b.createdAt) - new Date(a.createdAt));

  combined.slice(0, 20).forEach(item => {
    timelineContainer.appendChild(createPRIssueListItem(item));
  });
}
```

